{"key":"post-9498259","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9498259</id>\n<content>Bulk substrates should not be dunked for over a few hours.&amp;nbsp; The 24 hour suggestion is for cakes.&amp;nbsp; Simply put bulk trays in the sink and let the water fill the tray and gently run over the edges for a couple of hours, then pour off the water and return to fruiting conditions.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Read up on nomenclature.&amp;nbsp; You seem to be incorrectly using the word 'casing' to refer to a 'substrate tray'.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9498340</next>\n<prev>9498246</prev>\n<first>9498246</first>\n<last>9498736</last>\n<when>1230334264</when>\n<utime>12/27/08 01:31 AM</utime>\n</post>"}